args: I had to prove to Chelsea that I wasn't the only\none who had her back, so I gathered up everyone\nin the Halidom.
...Anyway, that's the plan. You guys up\nfor helpin' out?
We're with ya. And I'm sure we can find\nmore people to join the cause.
We'll send word to the sylvans in the\nwoods. They're gonna come in DROVES!
We shall ready the venue. It appears\nwe will have quite a few guests.
What are you up to, Luccy?
But I promise you this: You're about to\nhave a ton more friends.
A few days passed, and then I brought Chelsea\nto the courtyard.
Just a little mixer. Humans and sylvans\nalike, breakin' bread and hangin' out.
We rounded up some humans who wanted\nto know more about sylvan customs, and\nsome sylvans who were happy to teach.
So that's how y'all handle a bow, is it?\nFascinatin'!
The dyework here is incredible... I've never\nseen such unique colors!
But you know, if you add mulberries to\nyour dye, you can bring out even deeper\nshades.
Is that so? Let's give it a try!
They're all...getting along. And even\nLEARNING from each other! It's...
Just like what your mom and dad were\nstriving for, yeah?
All of us at the Halidom have realized\nsomething, traveling around so much.
There are lots of humans that wanna know\nmore about sylvan practices. Waaay more\nthan you'd think!
And on the flipside, there's a ton of sylvans\nthat wanna learn from humans, too.
You just happened to be surrounded by\na pretty insular crowd, I guess.
They all look so happy... Just like Mama\nand Papa did.
Nya ha ha! That was a solid one!
C'mon, it's just a friendly hello!\nI bet the humans here would take\nto it pretty quick.
Hey Chelsea, we're all gonna play a game\ntogether. Wanna join us?
'Course they do! You're the guest of honor.
And you've only really been talking to\nLuca, right?
Everyone else wants to get to know you\ntoo! Plus, between you and me, you can\ndo WAY better than my brother.
Everyone, gather round! We're gonna\nsplit into teams, and...
I... I don't know. My heart feels all warm\nand fluffy, but I'm crying...
Nobody's ever invited me to play before.\nWhat should I do, Luccy?
Well, I think step one is to smile.\nAnd step two is to get out there!
We're all just gonna goof off and get to\nknow each other better. That's how you\nmake friends, you know?
Thank you all for coming, everyone.\nNow, if you could all assist in the\nclean-up...
Sorry Cleo, but I've gotta bounce.\nI owe Chelsea some one-on-one time.
Thanks for today, Luccy. I made a lot\nof new friends.
Heck yeah you did!\nWasn't it easy?
It was. I guess I've kind of just been in my\nown world ever since my parents died.
Nobody here had any problem with me;\nI just convinced myself otherwise.
It sounds like you finally understand.
And now that that's cleared up, we actually\nneed to have another important discussion.\nYou mind?
I've thought a lot about how I wanna\ndeepen and broaden the exchange\nbetween human and sylvan cultures.
But to actually make it happen, we need\nthis world to find peace first.
I guess what I'm trying to say is, I'm really\nhonored that you care about me so much.\nBut right now, I...
Right now I can't think of anything but\nfighting alongside the prince and everyone.\nWe're fighting to save our whole world.

So I need you to understand that what
I said to you on the mountain wasn't a
proposal. I'm really sorry I gave you
the wrong idea.
No, I should be the one apologizing.\nYou tried to explain it multiple times,\nand I just didn't want to hear it.
I... I'm going to go help clean up. Bye!
Seemed like that went all right.\nGlad ya finally got through to her.
She's lived a very unfortunate life.\nBut I think it'll be different after today.
For your sake, I hope so. Bwa ha ha!
I thought that was the end of it, but...
Mornin' ChelWHAT ARE YOU DOIN'\nIN MY ROOM?!
I came to wake you up, silly! But you\nlooked so cute all snuggled up, I ended\nup just staring for a while. Tee hee!
Aw, man... Wait, I KNOW I locked the\ndoor last night!
I gave her a key. It's not good for a lock\nto be picked so frequently.
But if you're gonna wake him up,\nya gotta actually do it, Chelsea!
WhCleo? Sarisse?! What is going ON?!
I've tasked Chelsea with looking after\nyou for a while.
She'll keep you out of trouble.\nRiiight?
Yup! I'm gonna take the BEST care of you,\nLuccy. I'll prove to you that I'm prime\nwife material!
Er, did we not JUST clear up the whole\nmarriage thing?
Oh, we did. But that doesn't mean I'm\ngiving up on you. If anything, I like you\neven MORE now! Tee hee!
Besides, once you save the world and\njunk you'll be free to get married, right?\nThat's where I come in.
*sigh* Two steps forward, one step back...
Remember that cloth I got on our date?\nI made some outfits for our future kids;\none for a girl, and one for a boy.

Do you have any ideas for names?
I'd love to name the boy Luccy,
after my favorite person in the
whole world!

I have girl names picked out too, of course,
but we should probably lock in our
wedding details before all that.
Where do you want to have the ceremony?
We'll live happily ever after, one big\nhappy family! Tee hee heeee!
